Type: Package
Package: PostCard
Title: Prognostic covariate adjustment for estimation of average treatment
    effect
Version: 0.2.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Emilie", "Hoejbjerre-Frandsen", , "ehfd@novonordisk.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: The package maintainer <yourself@somewhere.net>
Description: Convenient functions for conducting analysis using prognostic
    covariate adjustment for linear models. The package contain a function
    that can generate normally distributed data in different data
    generating scenarios in order to determine the finite sample
    properties of prognostic covariate for linear models. This generated
    data can then be used as an input for the lm.hist.sim function, that
    estimates ATE, SD, power, type I error, etc. This function can also be
    used for a single pair of RCT and historical data.
